# Data Modelling – Normalization (Master Theory + Interview Style)
# What is Normalization?
## Theory
**Normalization** is the process of organizing data into well-structured tables to reduce:
* duplicate data
* update anomalies
* insert anomalies
* delete anomalies
* inconsistent data

Goal:
* cleaner schema
* better integrity
* easier maintenance

---

# Why Normalization Exists (Real Problem)

## Bad Table Example

| student_id | student_name | course | instructor |
| ---------- | ------------ | ------ | ---------- |
| 101        | Ravi         | SQL    | John       |
| 101        | Ravi         | Python | Mike       |
| 102        | Priya        | SQL    | John       |

Problems:

### Redundancy

Ravi repeated. John repeated.

### Update Anomaly

If John changes to Jonathan, must update multiple rows.

### Insert Anomaly

Cannot add new instructor unless student enrolled.

### Delete Anomaly

Delete last SQL student → lose instructor John data.

This is why normalization exists.

---

# Core Idea

Break one bad table into logical smaller tables.

Example:

## Students

| student_id | student_name |

## Courses

| course_id | course_name |

## Enrollments

| student_id | course_id |

## Instructors

| course_id | instructor |

Now cleaner.

