# Real World Example – E-commerce

At Amazon

## Bad Orders Table

| order_id | customer_name | customer_city | product_name | product_price |

Massive duplication.

## Better Normalized Design

### Customers

| customer_id | name | city |

### Products

| product_id | name | price |

### Orders

| order_id | customer_id |

### Order_Items

| order_id | product_id | qty |

This is scalable.

---

# Why OLTP Systems Prefer Normalization

Transactional systems at Uber, banks, ERPs often prefer normalized design because:

* fewer duplicates
* safer updates
* better consistency
* smaller storage

---

# Why Warehouses Often Denormalize

Analytics systems may prefer star schema instead of heavy normalization because:

* faster reads
* fewer joins
* BI friendly

This is key interview insight.

